1
00:00:09,426 --> 00:00:11,177
- Welcome.
- Table for two.

2
00:00:11,261 --> 00:00:12,262
Okay.

3
00:00:12,345 --> 00:00:13,722
Please sit wherever you'd like.

4
00:00:22,355 --> 00:00:23,565
- Towards the back?
- Yeah.

5
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:43,793
Oh, that sweater.

6
00:00:45,211 --> 00:00:46,171
I wore it.

7
00:00:47,547 --> 00:00:48,631
It suits you.

8
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:50,550
It's cute.

9
00:00:57,223 --> 00:00:58,391
Welcome.

10
00:00:59,559 --> 00:01:01,144
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

11
00:01:05,982 --> 00:01:08,234
- Call me when you're ready to order.
- Okay.

12
00:01:11,529 --> 00:01:14,574
- Want to eat a cake?
- Yeah.

13
00:01:21,456 --> 00:01:22,332
This one?

14
00:01:47,357 --> 00:01:48,358
Um…

15
00:01:51,194 --> 00:01:53,321
There's something I want to tell you.

16
00:01:55,323 --> 00:01:56,699
Is it okay if I speak first?

17
00:02:00,286 --> 00:02:02,997
I only ask since you said you wanted
to tell me something too.

18
00:02:03,081 --> 00:02:04,124
Yeah.

19
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:07,794
I don't mind.

20
00:02:08,837 --> 00:02:10,088
You can go first.

21
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:12,090
Thanks.

22
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:19,222
So…

23
00:02:21,891 --> 00:02:23,101
The thing is…

24
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:28,982
The truth is…

25
00:02:33,862 --> 00:02:35,822
I've been a really horrible person.

26
00:02:39,742 --> 00:02:43,830
While we've been going out,

27
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:47,000
I cheated on you a few times

28
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:50,378
and have been attracted to other people.

29
00:02:55,508 --> 00:02:56,676
Yeah, and…

30
00:02:57,635 --> 00:03:00,513
I guess I tend to

31
00:03:01,389 --> 00:03:04,934
fall for people much more easily
than others do.

32
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:07,353
But

33
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:11,983
I’m afraid of opening up
and facing someone,

34
00:03:12,775 --> 00:03:13,776
and so

35
00:03:14,402 --> 00:03:17,864
I end up cheating with people
I don’t actually have to be serious with.

36
00:03:18,907 --> 00:03:19,741
Yeah.

37
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:21,451
And…

38
00:03:23,995 --> 00:03:25,121
How should I say this?

39
00:03:27,457 --> 00:03:29,751
I don't really
understand it myself either,

40
00:03:33,463 --> 00:03:35,298
but at a certain point in my life,

41
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:41,888
it seems I lost the ability to actually
be in a relationship with just one person.

42
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:47,393
And?

43
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:50,772
And so…

44
00:03:51,522 --> 00:03:55,443
I know perfectly well that
telling you this benefits you in no way

45
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:58,738
and that it's a completely selfish thing.

46
00:03:59,781 --> 00:04:01,324
I know that,

47
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:04,827
but I felt
that I had to tell you everything.

48
00:04:06,996 --> 00:04:08,581
I felt that I had to be honest

49
00:04:09,332 --> 00:04:12,627
and tell you how I feel,
including what I just told you just now.

50
00:04:16,172 --> 00:04:17,215
I see.

51
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:28,685
Well,

52
00:04:29,185 --> 00:04:31,396
I'll listen to everything you have to say.

53
00:04:34,023 --> 00:04:35,566
Please tell me everything.

54
00:04:42,573 --> 00:04:43,616
So…

55
00:04:46,869 --> 00:04:47,912
<i>From there,</i>

56
00:04:48,871 --> 00:04:51,499
<i>I told Yukio everything</i>
<i>I had been hiding from him,</i>

57
00:04:52,417 --> 00:04:54,460
<i>one after the other.</i>

58
00:04:56,587 --> 00:04:58,631
<i>How I cheated on him several times.</i>

59
00:05:00,049 --> 00:05:03,469
<i>But how I stopped doing that recently.</i>

60
00:05:05,513 --> 00:05:07,473
<i>I didn't mention him by name,</i>

61
00:05:07,974 --> 00:05:10,184
<i>but I told Yukio</i>
<i>how I was attracted to Mr. Yamada.</i>

62
00:05:12,937 --> 00:05:16,149
<i>And how Mr. Yamada</i>
<i>knew about Yukio's existence</i>

63
00:05:17,066 --> 00:05:17,984
<i>because</i>

64
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:21,571
<i>I didn't hide from him</i>
<i>that I had a boyfriend.</i>

65
00:05:23,948 --> 00:05:26,534
<i>I told him how</i>
<i>Mr. Yamada also has a girlfriend.</i>

66
00:05:29,078 --> 00:05:29,912
<i>But</i>

67
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:32,623
<i>how we were still attracted to each other.</i>

68
00:05:34,751 --> 00:05:37,253
<i>How I always told Mr. Yamada everything</i>

69
00:05:37,754 --> 00:05:40,715
<i>that I couldn't confide in Yukio.</i>

70
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:48,056
The truth is

71
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:50,600
the person

72
00:05:51,309 --> 00:05:54,020
I really wanted to confide in,

73
00:05:55,271 --> 00:05:57,982
and talk to about the pain I was feeling,
was you.

74
00:05:59,108 --> 00:06:01,986
But the desire to do that,
and the reason for my pain

75
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:03,946
were too contradictory.

76
00:06:06,032 --> 00:06:07,116
But

77
00:06:08,576 --> 00:06:12,413
if I could talk about it,
and share this burden with someone,

78
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:15,166
the person I would want
to talk about it with the most

79
00:06:15,249 --> 00:06:16,626
is you.

80
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:19,670
That's what I kept confiding
to the other person about.

81
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:22,882
Then?

82
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:27,804
What did that person say?

83
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:29,639
Oh.

84
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:32,558
He said he felt the same way too.

85
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:34,519
What?

86
00:06:35,603 --> 00:06:38,689
He said that his girlfriend
was the most important person to him

87
00:06:38,773 --> 00:06:43,069
and that she's the one he wanted
to confide in the most.

88
00:06:46,948 --> 00:06:47,824
Um…

89
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:52,245
Isn't that really selfish?

90
00:06:52,328 --> 00:06:54,163
That goes for both you and him.

91
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:57,834
Yeah.

92
00:06:59,127 --> 00:07:01,754
Wait a minute. So that person

93
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:04,757
likes his girlfriend more?

94
00:07:04,841 --> 00:07:07,468
It's not that he likes you more
than his girlfriend?

95
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:11,180
You were okay with that?

96
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:14,142
It didn't bother you?

97
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:16,018
You were okay with it?

98
00:07:18,729 --> 00:07:19,939
Um…

99
00:07:20,022 --> 00:07:23,985
So that person's girlfriend
no longer exists.

100
00:07:25,278 --> 00:07:26,195
Doesn't exist?

101
00:07:28,197 --> 00:07:29,574
What do you mean?

102
00:07:30,074 --> 00:07:31,534
She passed away.

103
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:33,744
Huh.

104
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:38,666
That person's girlfriend
is no longer alive.

105
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:44,213
But he hasn't realized that yet.

106
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:47,800
No, it's not that he doesn't realize it.

107
00:07:48,509 --> 00:07:51,512
He's going through life,
believing that she's still alive.

108
00:07:52,513 --> 00:07:56,267
And so, he had resolved
never to fall in love with anyone else.

109
00:07:56,350 --> 00:08:00,730
But he was struggling
because he felt an attraction towards me.

110
00:08:05,735 --> 00:08:07,069
He's someone

111
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:11,699
who always seemed to have death
lingering close by.

112
00:08:15,661 --> 00:08:18,915
At first, I might've stayed close to him
because I was concerned about him.

113
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:21,501
Because I wanted him to live.

114
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:27,840
But isn't that…

115
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:32,887
Isn't that the most cowardly thing to do?

116
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:37,391
Pulling that "I feel like dying,"
or the "I'm really messed up" card.

117
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:43,731
And then you felt the need to stay by him
because you were concerned for him?

118
00:08:45,274 --> 00:08:48,402
You can't call that love.

119
00:08:50,112 --> 00:08:52,990
It's cowardly to exploit another person's

120
00:08:53,699 --> 00:08:55,034
kindness.

121
00:08:56,953 --> 00:09:01,624
But I just ended up feeling that way
on my own.

122
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:05,586
- So it's not his fault.
- But that's basically taking

123
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:06,921
someone hostage.

124
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:13,135
Making someone feel
like they might die if you’re not around…

125
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:21,769
That’s the one thing I hate
more than anything.

126
00:09:30,444 --> 00:09:31,362
But…

127
00:09:32,989 --> 00:09:35,199
you wouldn't want him to die either, huh?

128
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:44,375
The thing is…

129
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:49,964
He always
seemed to enjoy the time he spent with me.

130
00:09:51,007 --> 00:09:52,883
But for him,

131
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:56,137
that very sense of enjoyment
was directly tied to feelings of guilt.

132
00:09:58,389 --> 00:10:00,349
So that led him to more torment.

133
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,021
So, yeah…

134
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:08,274
Well…

135
00:10:09,233 --> 00:10:10,818
That's everything.

136
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:12,778
I…

137
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:18,284
I honestly reached a point
where I didn't know what to do anymore.

138
00:10:19,577 --> 00:10:22,121
But then I realized that I couldn't

139
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:24,373
just keep going on like this

140
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:27,835
and stay silent
while continuing to be with you.

141
00:10:28,919 --> 00:10:30,421
That's why I told you everything.

142
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:36,385
And?

143
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:42,850
What is it that you want to do, Ayana?

144
00:10:43,851 --> 00:10:45,853
Do you still want to be with me?

145
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:50,149
Yes.

146
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:53,361
I see.

147
00:10:57,948 --> 00:11:00,701
So, what's the situation
with that person now?

148
00:11:02,703 --> 00:11:03,871
We had a conversation where we agreed

149
00:11:03,954 --> 00:11:07,166
not to see each other anymore,
and we haven't met at all since then.

150
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:12,922
Although there's a possibility we might
cross paths for work-related things.

151
00:11:13,005 --> 00:11:14,006
I see.

152
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:17,051
That person is all right now?

153
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:22,098
- Yeah. A lot better.
- I see.

154
00:11:35,736 --> 00:11:36,695
Oh.

155
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:51,168
Happy birthday.

156
00:11:53,754 --> 00:11:55,339
It's that color.

157
00:11:56,465 --> 00:11:58,342
Onsen blue.

158
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:02,221
I chose that color for you.

159
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:10,581
Ayana,

160
00:13:14,418 --> 00:13:15,377
let's break up.

161
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:17,671
I don't want to.

162
00:13:18,339 --> 00:13:20,466
You know, I kind of sensed it.

163
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:26,472
I sensed that something was off with you.

164
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,808
I knew you were suffering over something.

165
00:13:29,892 --> 00:13:30,935
I don't want to.

166
00:13:35,481 --> 00:13:38,526
Can you listen to what I have to say too?

167
00:13:39,026 --> 00:13:40,027
I don't want to.

168
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:43,030
Listen to me.
I listened to what you had to say.

169
00:13:45,324 --> 00:13:47,326
I want you to hear me out.

170
00:14:17,147 --> 00:14:19,233
Okay. Please let me hear it.

171
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:26,115
I actually

172
00:14:27,783 --> 00:14:30,578
noticed something was off
even before we went to the onsen.

173
00:14:31,745 --> 00:14:33,706
In fact, at Christmas,

174
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:37,751
remember I asked if you wanted to
move in together sometime around summer?

175
00:14:38,627 --> 00:14:42,673
When I asked you that question,
your reaction

176
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:44,884
seemed a little off.

177
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:51,807
I didn't want to admit it,

178
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:54,894
but I had a feeling

179
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:59,690
it was going to end soon.

180
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:02,484
That maybe it was all coming to an end.

181
00:15:05,237 --> 00:15:07,781
That’s why I suggested
we go on that onsen trip.

182
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:13,412
I actually thought you might turn me down.
But I'm glad you had a good time.

183
00:15:14,496 --> 00:15:15,831
I had a blast too.

184
00:15:18,959 --> 00:15:21,337
I gave you that sweater as a gift.

185
00:15:23,088 --> 00:15:25,591
And I asked you to knit me a scarf.

186
00:15:27,551 --> 00:15:30,262
I thought that maybe,
just while you were knitting the scarf,

187
00:15:34,224 --> 00:15:37,603
you’d be thinking about me.

188
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:44,026
I had no intention of accepting it,
but I had you knit it.

189
00:15:44,610 --> 00:15:45,736
I'm a jerk, huh?

190
00:15:52,326 --> 00:15:56,288
Today,
even if you hadn't told me everything,

191
00:15:57,581 --> 00:16:00,334
I was planning on breaking up with you.

192
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:04,505
That’s why

193
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:08,300
I picked the laundromat where we first met
as our meeting spot.

194
00:16:10,719 --> 00:16:13,222
This is my first time coming to this cafe.

195
00:16:14,723 --> 00:16:17,559
The thing is, we could've talked
at my salon.

196
00:16:18,435 --> 00:16:20,938
I could've chosen to go there instead.

197
00:16:21,021 --> 00:16:22,231
Since we're closed today.

198
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:25,734
But…

199
00:16:28,487 --> 00:16:32,324
if I did that, I’d be reminded of you
every single day when I work.

200
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:39,331
It would be too painful
to be reminded of you while I work.

201
00:16:45,921 --> 00:16:46,839
That's why

202
00:16:47,464 --> 00:16:51,218
I wanted to talk at a place
I’d never have to set foot in again.

203
00:17:01,729 --> 00:17:02,646
I…

204
00:17:07,776 --> 00:17:09,445
like you, Ayana.

205
00:17:10,863 --> 00:17:11,780
I still like you.

206
00:17:15,325 --> 00:17:18,579
That's why
I can't continue this relationship.

207
00:17:29,048 --> 00:17:31,592
And you know Sae?
The girl that works for me?

208
00:17:34,136 --> 00:17:36,889
I might start seeing her
after we break up.

209
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:42,102
She had told me that she likes me,
and we've even gone out on a few dates.

210
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:45,439
She's a really nice person.

211
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:50,527
In fact,

212
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:55,449
I've been getting advice from her
about you.

213
00:18:02,289 --> 00:18:03,207
I see.

214
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:05,542
Yeah.

215
00:18:12,716 --> 00:18:13,884
That's all.

216
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:18,597
You told me everything, so I told you too.

217
00:18:27,356 --> 00:18:30,150
That Sae that you talked about?

218
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:32,277
Yeah? What about Sae?

219
00:18:35,864 --> 00:18:40,452
You didn't have to tell me about Sae,
but you did.

220
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:42,913
Was it for my sake?

221
00:18:45,582 --> 00:18:49,128
Did you tell me, so that it would
lessen my feelings of guilt?

222
00:18:51,046 --> 00:18:53,090
Saying that you cheated on me too?

223
00:18:53,173 --> 00:18:56,635
It's not like that at all.
I'm not that nice.

224
00:18:58,345 --> 00:18:59,805
Plus, I didn't cheat.

225
00:19:16,238 --> 00:19:17,489
Let's break up.

226
00:19:22,035 --> 00:19:23,287
Please.

227
00:19:34,965 --> 00:19:36,091
Okay.

228
00:19:39,887 --> 00:19:40,888
Thank you.

229
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:45,893
I'm sorry.

230
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:51,982
I am too.

231
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,401
I'm sorry.

232
00:20:07,706 --> 00:20:08,957
Can I…

233
00:20:11,376 --> 00:20:13,837
Can I just ask for one last favor?

234
00:20:16,924 --> 00:20:17,925
What is it?

235
00:20:20,761 --> 00:20:22,596
Can you cut my hair?

236
00:20:23,096 --> 00:20:25,515
Just a trim is fine. Please.

237
00:20:26,683 --> 00:20:30,646
I just said that I don't want to discuss
the breakup at the salon.

238
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:34,524
Yeah, so we won't talk about it.
I promise.

239
00:20:37,945 --> 00:20:39,363
Even if we are going to talk…

240
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:44,034
Let's just reminisce.

241
00:20:45,452 --> 00:20:48,830
Let's talk about something
as trivial as possible. Just dumb stuff.

242
00:20:56,171 --> 00:20:58,715
You're so selfish.

243
00:21:29,579 --> 00:21:30,580
Welcome.

244
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:42,050
Opening the roller shutter
and coming inside brings back memories.

245
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:44,886
Brings back memories?

246
00:21:44,970 --> 00:21:47,097
It's part of daily life for me.

247
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:50,434
We talked about this
on the day we first met, huh?

248
00:21:50,517 --> 00:21:52,436
The ordinary and the extraordinary.

249
00:21:52,519 --> 00:21:53,478
Yeah.

250
00:22:40,859 --> 00:22:42,819
How's the temperature?

251
00:22:44,446 --> 00:22:45,947
It's good.

252
00:22:51,119 --> 00:22:54,081
- I'm going to shampoo your hair now.
- Yes, please.

253
00:23:18,605 --> 00:23:19,439
How do you like it?

254
00:23:20,065 --> 00:23:21,733
It's good.

255
00:23:21,817 --> 00:23:22,651
Okay.

256
00:23:23,276 --> 00:23:24,277
Cute.

257
00:23:30,283 --> 00:23:33,120
All done.

258
00:23:33,203 --> 00:23:35,497
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

259
00:23:39,376 --> 00:23:40,502
I feel refreshed.

260
00:23:40,585 --> 00:23:42,838
I made you refreshed.

261
00:23:49,553 --> 00:23:50,470
Hey,

262
00:23:51,429 --> 00:23:53,140
during our trip to the onsen,

263
00:23:54,015 --> 00:23:56,309
remember how we talked about the mouth?

264
00:23:57,310 --> 00:23:59,396
You said the mouth has too many functions,

265
00:23:59,479 --> 00:24:02,399
so it would be nice to have a mouth here
just for speaking.

266
00:24:02,482 --> 00:24:04,442
Remember we discussed that?

267
00:24:04,526 --> 00:24:06,319
- Yeah.
- About that…

268
00:24:07,195 --> 00:24:08,405
Come this way.

269
00:24:09,406 --> 00:24:10,824
Stand right here.

270
00:24:12,367 --> 00:24:13,410
What is it?

271
00:24:14,995 --> 00:24:17,330
Remember how
it kind of ended up like a dance?

272
00:24:17,414 --> 00:24:19,499
I talked to you like this.

273
00:24:22,085 --> 00:24:24,087
And I talked to you like this.

274
00:24:24,171 --> 00:24:26,173
Then I replied back like this.

275
00:24:28,008 --> 00:24:29,259
And I replied like this.

276
00:24:29,342 --> 00:24:31,469
Or we turned around in circles.

277
00:24:31,553 --> 00:24:34,055
You would hear me speak like this.

278
00:24:35,182 --> 00:24:36,933
And you heard me speak like this.

279
00:24:37,017 --> 00:24:40,729
Yeah, and we both agreed
that it was a bit chaotic.

280
00:24:40,812 --> 00:24:42,439
We said the movements would kick up dust.

281
00:24:42,522 --> 00:24:44,524
So we sat down and resumed eating.

282
00:24:45,692 --> 00:24:47,319
Yeah, I remember that.

283
00:24:47,903 --> 00:24:49,029
What about that?

284
00:24:51,031 --> 00:24:54,868
So I realized something later on.

285
00:24:55,869 --> 00:24:58,205
Stand still right there.

286
00:24:58,288 --> 00:24:59,873
Stand straight.

287
00:25:05,045 --> 00:25:06,504
Don't you realize something?

288
00:25:08,381 --> 00:25:09,883
What is it?

289
00:25:13,178 --> 00:25:14,971
When we face each other like this,

290
00:25:17,515 --> 00:25:22,062
even if we don't move an inch,
my left ear and your right ear

291
00:25:22,145 --> 00:25:24,064
are close to each other,

292
00:25:25,398 --> 00:25:31,154
and your left ear
is close to my right ear.

293
00:25:31,238 --> 00:25:32,364
You're right.

294
00:25:33,198 --> 00:25:35,992
- Very true.
- Yup.

295
00:25:36,910 --> 00:25:38,245
- You know…
- Yeah?

296
00:25:39,204 --> 00:25:40,247
You know,

297
00:25:41,539 --> 00:25:43,500
we were caught up
in the daily hustle and bustle,

298
00:25:44,084 --> 00:25:46,419
and never took the time
to face each other.

299
00:25:47,587 --> 00:25:49,381
And that's why we failed to notice this.

300
00:25:50,257 --> 00:25:53,301
I found myself thinking

301
00:25:55,512 --> 00:25:58,098
that if we had faced each other honestly,

302
00:25:58,890 --> 00:26:02,894
perhaps everything would have been
as simple as this.

303
00:26:05,647 --> 00:26:06,606
You may be right.

304
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:24,582
Yukio.

305
00:26:24,666 --> 00:26:25,917
Yeah?

306
00:26:32,757 --> 00:26:34,009
Yukio.

307
00:26:35,969 --> 00:26:37,012
I…

308
00:26:41,683 --> 00:26:42,934
I think

309
00:26:44,561 --> 00:26:47,147
I'll quickly fall in love
with someone again.

310
00:26:51,609 --> 00:26:52,986
I don't think

311
00:26:53,737 --> 00:26:55,697
I'm suited for marriage at all.

312
00:26:57,324 --> 00:26:58,408
Honestly,

313
00:26:58,491 --> 00:27:01,411
I don't think I'm really cut out
for dating,

314
00:27:02,912 --> 00:27:05,582
or being in a relationship
with any one specific person.

315
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:11,129
Yeah.

316
00:27:13,006 --> 00:27:14,049
Even so…

317
00:27:15,842 --> 00:27:16,968
Even so,

318
00:27:18,762 --> 00:27:20,263
the fact that I was able to spend

319
00:27:21,056 --> 00:27:23,016
a little over a year together with you,

320
00:27:25,477 --> 00:27:29,356
was entirely because you
always cherished me.

321
00:27:32,067 --> 00:27:32,984
Um…

322
00:27:37,113 --> 00:27:38,198
This…

323
00:27:39,949 --> 00:27:42,243
might sound like nothing but a lie,

324
00:27:44,204 --> 00:27:45,246
but I

325
00:27:47,957 --> 00:27:51,211
consider you
the most important person to me.

326
00:27:53,338 --> 00:27:55,215
You're the last person
I’d ever want to lose.

327
00:27:57,384 --> 00:27:58,218
Yeah.

328
00:27:59,052 --> 00:28:03,056
And so I kept asking myself
why I cheated on you time and time again.

329
00:28:06,726 --> 00:28:11,147
I can't really understand it myself.

330
00:28:22,826 --> 00:28:24,702
Maybe because it was necessary.

331
00:28:25,829 --> 00:28:26,663
What?

332
00:28:29,082 --> 00:28:32,001
I think you did it out of necessity.

333
00:28:35,547 --> 00:28:39,092
You know, this might be
an exaggerated way of explaining it…

334
00:28:42,470 --> 00:28:47,726
But maybe, you're the type that will die
if you don't keep doing that.

335
00:28:51,146 --> 00:28:54,983
Sort of like how some fish die
if they ever stop swimming.

336
00:28:56,151 --> 00:28:57,235
Like tuna or something?

337
00:28:57,318 --> 00:28:59,320
Yeah, like tuna. Or the skipjack tuna.

338
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:06,494
Then…

339
00:29:07,495 --> 00:29:09,456
I wonder if I'll always be like this.

340
00:29:13,501 --> 00:29:15,086
In the end,

341
00:29:16,087 --> 00:29:18,631
maybe I’m the only one I truly care about.

342
00:29:18,715 --> 00:29:20,175
Maybe I'm just selfish,

343
00:29:25,305 --> 00:29:27,849
and don't truly love anyone else at all.

344
00:29:30,101 --> 00:29:33,271
I go around saying
that I fall for people easily,

345
00:29:34,606 --> 00:29:36,691
but if I truly loved them,

346
00:29:36,775 --> 00:29:39,611
I wouldn't get attracted to someone else
so easily, right?

347
00:29:43,573 --> 00:29:44,783
If that’s the case,

348
00:29:45,575 --> 00:29:48,620
maybe I’d be better off
not going out with anyone anymore.

349
00:29:48,703 --> 00:29:50,663
I just don’t get it anymore.

350
00:29:52,457 --> 00:29:54,542
What does it mean to love someone?

351
00:29:55,210 --> 00:29:56,836
What's romance?

352
00:30:05,762 --> 00:30:06,596
What is it?

353
00:30:07,222 --> 00:30:09,390
Sorry, I didn't mean to laugh.

354
00:30:10,558 --> 00:30:11,643
What is it? Just tell me.

355
00:30:12,894 --> 00:30:14,854
I just thought, how would I know?

356
00:30:16,147 --> 00:30:16,981
What?

357
00:30:18,733 --> 00:30:21,069
How would I know?

358
00:30:21,778 --> 00:30:25,198
And I really don't care.

359
00:30:26,658 --> 00:30:27,617
You're horrible.

360
00:30:33,915 --> 00:30:36,668
You'll find someone you like soon enough.

361
00:30:36,751 --> 00:30:38,920
By tomorrow, you'll be sleeping
with another guy.

362
00:30:39,003 --> 00:30:41,506
Hey! You're such a jerk.

363
00:30:45,677 --> 00:30:47,095
You know,

364
00:30:49,931 --> 00:30:52,100
forget about any guilt
you have towards me.

365
00:30:55,436 --> 00:30:57,230
Please don't torment yourself.

366
00:31:00,775 --> 00:31:04,153
No matter who you date,
or how many people you sleep with,

367
00:31:04,237 --> 00:31:07,073
if you’re enjoying yourself,
then I think that’s perfectly fine.

368
00:31:11,119 --> 00:31:12,120
But…

369
00:31:15,748 --> 00:31:17,959
if that causes you pain…

370
00:31:20,753 --> 00:31:23,047
If doing those things

371
00:31:23,131 --> 00:31:25,508
makes it hard for you to breathe,

372
00:31:28,595 --> 00:31:30,597
then maybe you can
use that chance to make changes.

373
00:31:38,396 --> 00:31:40,899
Not that there's anything
I can do for you.

374
00:31:48,031 --> 00:31:49,073
You're right.

375
00:32:01,377 --> 00:32:02,253
All right.

376
00:32:04,005 --> 00:32:05,298
Today's price

377
00:32:06,215 --> 00:32:09,469
for a haircut and shampoo
will be 7,500 yen.

378
00:32:10,887 --> 00:32:12,305
You're charging me?

379
00:32:12,388 --> 00:32:15,016
Of course. We're not dating anymore.

380
00:32:17,060 --> 00:32:18,061
You're right.

381
00:32:19,312 --> 00:32:20,188
I'll pay.

382
00:32:20,271 --> 00:32:21,814
I'm just kidding.

383
00:32:21,898 --> 00:32:23,024
No, I'll pay.

384
00:32:23,107 --> 00:32:25,234
- No, I was really kidding.
- Okay.

385
00:32:28,404 --> 00:32:29,530
Really, that was a joke.

386
00:32:34,494 --> 00:32:36,913
Would it be okay to come back here
as a customer?

387
00:32:39,791 --> 00:32:43,086
I don't think so. Sae wouldn't like that.

388
00:32:46,255 --> 00:32:47,966
Please don't come back.

389
00:32:49,842 --> 00:32:50,677
Okay.

390
00:32:52,220 --> 00:32:53,054
Got it.

391
00:32:54,597 --> 00:32:55,682
I won't come again.

392
00:33:01,270 --> 00:33:02,689
Today's haircut is free.

393
00:33:03,731 --> 00:33:04,941
Your last free haircut.

394
00:33:07,151 --> 00:33:08,027
Thank you.

395
00:33:12,991 --> 00:33:13,825
Bye.

396
00:33:14,909 --> 00:33:15,743
Bye.

397
00:33:23,501 --> 00:33:25,211
Thank you very much.

398
00:34:24,187 --> 00:34:26,230
What's the matter?

399
00:34:29,233 --> 00:34:31,110
I left once and came back.

400
00:34:32,236 --> 00:34:34,489
So can't we start over
by meeting each other again?

401
00:34:37,116 --> 00:34:38,034
Because look,

402
00:34:39,202 --> 00:34:40,870
when you get to know a stranger,

403
00:34:40,953 --> 00:34:43,081
you won't be wary
of that person anymore, right?

404
00:34:43,998 --> 00:34:46,876
If you get to know me better,
maybe you won't be wary of me at all.

405
00:34:59,180 --> 00:35:00,264
I'm sorry.

406
00:35:04,769 --> 00:35:08,981
I just don't feel like I want
to know you any better.

407
00:35:14,445 --> 00:35:15,446
I see.

408
00:35:19,283 --> 00:35:20,368
That's understandable.

409
00:35:26,916 --> 00:35:27,917
Bye.

410
00:35:49,981 --> 00:35:52,108
<i>In this world,</i>

411
00:35:52,191 --> 00:35:56,279
<i>while everyone else but me</i>
<i>can still have their hair cut by Yukio,</i>

412
00:35:57,655 --> 00:36:01,784
<i>I alone have become the one person</i>
<i>who can never receive that service.</i>

413
00:36:10,334 --> 00:36:13,838
<i>If the very act of dating,</i>
<i>or the very nature</i>

414
00:36:14,338 --> 00:36:18,885
<i>of a romantic relationship,</i>
<i>entails the possibility of losing not only</i>

415
00:36:19,385 --> 00:36:22,180
<i>the past and present</i>
<i>shared with that person,</i>

416
00:36:23,431 --> 00:36:27,894
<i>but also the future</i>
<i>that might have been shared with them,</i>

417
00:36:28,853 --> 00:36:32,064
EMPTYNESS

418
00:36:32,148 --> 00:36:36,152
<i>then I want nothing to do</i>
<i>with romance ever again.</i>

419
00:36:39,947 --> 00:36:41,407
CARESS

420
00:36:41,490 --> 00:36:43,659
<i>But at the same time,</i>

421
00:36:44,827 --> 00:36:47,872
<i>even though the sorrow I feel</i>
<i>is undeniably genuine,</i>

422
00:36:48,664 --> 00:36:51,834
<i>I realize that deep down,</i>

423
00:36:52,835 --> 00:36:55,671
<i>a part of me feels a sense of relief.</i>

424
00:36:57,757 --> 00:36:59,008
<i>I wonder</i>

425
00:36:59,634 --> 00:37:03,012
<i>if this relief stems</i>
<i>from having been able to set Yukio free,</i>

426
00:37:04,138 --> 00:37:07,391
<i>or if it comes from the liberating feeling</i>
<i>of finally being alone.</i>

427
00:37:09,435 --> 00:37:10,853
<i>In any case,</i>

428
00:37:11,812 --> 00:37:14,315
<i>I find stability in being alone,</i>

429
00:37:15,024 --> 00:37:17,568
<i>and I feel a sense of relief</i>
<i>at having returned to a state</i>

430
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:21,280
<i>where falling for someone</i>
<i>is no longer something forbidden.</i>

431
00:37:33,042 --> 00:37:34,961
- Hey.
- Hey.

432
00:37:44,387 --> 00:37:45,471
It's good to see you.

433
00:37:51,602 --> 00:37:52,770
It's good to see you.

434
00:37:52,853 --> 00:37:54,939
There's nothing good about it.

435
00:37:57,233 --> 00:37:59,026
I was dumped!

436
00:38:02,571 --> 00:38:04,198
Why?

437
00:38:04,282 --> 00:38:06,450
Why does Ayana have to get dumped?

438
00:38:08,494 --> 00:38:09,328
Shut up.

439
00:38:10,162 --> 00:38:11,205
Damn it.

440
00:38:30,808 --> 00:38:31,809
You can have it.

441
00:38:34,562 --> 00:38:38,274
I told you that I can't wear scarves
or wool because it makes my neck itchy.

442
00:38:39,442 --> 00:38:40,484
Did you?

443
00:38:43,529 --> 00:38:44,947
Then I'll unravel it.

444
00:38:45,740 --> 00:38:48,117
- Really?
- Yeah, I'm going to unravel it.

445
00:38:49,452 --> 00:38:52,038
But why? You went to all the trouble
of knitting it.

446
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:57,960
Can you hold this?

447
00:38:59,337 --> 00:39:00,379
Hold onto it.

448
00:39:02,089 --> 00:39:03,174
Hold right here.

449
00:39:09,347 --> 00:39:11,015
What a waste.

450
00:40:22,169 --> 00:40:23,421
Hey.

451
00:40:24,380 --> 00:40:25,548
What is it?

452
00:40:26,173 --> 00:40:27,675
Can I have that yarn?

453
00:40:28,717 --> 00:40:30,553
Sure. But why?

454
00:40:31,512 --> 00:40:32,888
Well,

455
00:40:33,472 --> 00:40:36,600
there’s a chance that someday
you might knit me a scarf, right?

456
00:40:37,101 --> 00:40:39,019
So, I’ll toughen myself up
against the itchiness.

457
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:42,523
Keep dreaming.
That will never happen in the future.

458
00:40:43,691 --> 00:40:45,109
That's fine.

459
00:40:46,110 --> 00:40:49,613
Just the possibility of that happening
gives me the will to live.

460
00:40:51,073 --> 00:40:53,617
You're trying to sound really cool.

461
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:55,202
But you're an idiot.

462
00:40:56,245 --> 00:40:58,038
No I'm not.

463
00:41:03,377 --> 00:41:04,587
- Here.
- Wow.

464
00:41:04,670 --> 00:41:06,088
Thanks.

465
00:41:22,563 --> 00:41:24,982
You know, you look best
when you're smiling.

466
00:41:25,524 --> 00:41:27,860
Though I like it when you're
deep in thought too.

467
00:41:30,154 --> 00:41:31,405
What the heck.

468
00:41:35,075 --> 00:41:36,869
But I guess it's not just you.

469
00:41:36,952 --> 00:41:40,331
Everyone is better off smiling. Probably.

470
00:41:43,209 --> 00:41:44,418
Yeah, of course.

471
00:41:51,759 --> 00:41:53,802
Say no to war!

472
00:41:55,930 --> 00:41:57,097
War?

473
00:42:01,310 --> 00:42:02,811
Say no to war!

474
00:42:06,232 --> 00:42:09,610
I wish both war and romance
would just disappear.

475
00:42:11,278 --> 00:42:12,821
Let romance live.

476
00:42:13,572 --> 00:42:15,115
Let romance live?

477
00:42:15,991 --> 00:42:19,119
You have no luck with romance,
but you want romance to live? How funny.

478
00:42:19,745 --> 00:42:22,873
Hey! Let me dream.

479
00:42:22,957 --> 00:42:26,544
Whether my love life succeeds or fails
is entirely up to you.

480
00:42:26,627 --> 00:42:27,753
True.

481
00:42:30,631 --> 00:42:32,800
I can't believe you agree to it.

482
00:42:37,930 --> 00:42:41,225
Oh man, I shouldn't have
unraveled that after all.

483
00:42:41,308 --> 00:42:42,893
Kotaro, put it back the way it was.

484
00:42:42,977 --> 00:42:44,228
What?

485
00:42:44,311 --> 00:42:46,855
That's why I told you not to do it.
Didn't I?

486
00:42:46,939 --> 00:42:48,148
Come on, start knitting.

487
00:42:49,024 --> 00:42:51,068
You're insane.

488
00:42:55,489 --> 00:42:58,075
Where does the yarn begin and end?

489
00:43:00,911 --> 00:43:02,121
I can't knit this!

490
00:43:03,414 --> 00:43:04,540
You can do it.

491
00:43:05,207 --> 00:43:07,501
<i>I found out later,</i>

492
00:43:07,585 --> 00:43:09,587
<i>that from that night</i>
<i>to the following morning,</i>

493
00:43:10,170 --> 00:43:11,714
<i>a bunch of red bumps</i>

494
00:43:11,797 --> 00:43:14,883
<i>apparently broke out on Kotaro's neck.</i>

495
00:43:17,344 --> 00:43:19,138
<i>Kotaro is an idiot, but sometimes</i>

496
00:43:19,221 --> 00:43:20,764
<i>it's a real blessing.</i>

497
00:43:22,266 --> 00:43:23,851
I'll become immune to wool.

498
00:43:31,817 --> 00:43:38,532
ONE YEAR LATER
APRIL 2027

499
00:43:42,911 --> 00:43:45,080
AYANA TSUCHIDA
WINTER AND LIGHT BLUE

500
00:43:45,164 --> 00:43:46,915
<i>A year has passed since then,</i>

501
00:43:47,583 --> 00:43:48,792
<i>and I published</i>

502
00:43:48,876 --> 00:43:52,129
<i>a novel based on the romance</i>
<i>experienced by En and myself.</i>

503
00:43:52,963 --> 00:43:55,966
<i>Titled,</i> Winter and Light Blue.

504
00:44:04,141 --> 00:44:05,142
I'll refill your water.

505
00:44:05,225 --> 00:44:06,226
Thank you.

506
00:44:07,645 --> 00:44:09,229
<i>And I have</i>

507
00:44:09,980 --> 00:44:13,233
<i>slowly begun writing a new novel.</i>

508
00:44:22,951 --> 00:44:25,788
<i>In the year since Yukio and I broke up,</i>

509
00:44:27,623 --> 00:44:31,502
<i>I have not had a steady boyfriend.</i>

510
00:44:48,686 --> 00:44:50,479
<i>On one sunny day in spring,</i>

511
00:44:51,397 --> 00:44:56,068
<i>En invited me to go strawberry picking.</i>

512
00:44:56,151 --> 00:44:58,779
<i>On a whim, I decided to invite Kotaro</i>
<i>to come along as well.</i>

513
00:45:04,618 --> 00:45:05,494
Nice.

514
00:45:05,577 --> 00:45:06,578
- It's pretty.
- Yeah.

515
00:45:06,662 --> 00:45:07,621
Nice.

516
00:45:21,718 --> 00:45:22,553
Um…

517
00:45:23,137 --> 00:45:24,805
Who did you come here with before, En?

518
00:45:25,556 --> 00:45:26,640
What?

519
00:45:26,723 --> 00:45:28,976
Did you come here before
with your boyfriend?

520
00:45:29,059 --> 00:45:31,145
Or was it your girlfriends?

521
00:45:32,229 --> 00:45:34,690
I came with a male friend.

522
00:45:36,108 --> 00:45:40,737
A male friend? Did that friendship
progress into something?

523
00:45:41,405 --> 00:45:42,531
Progress?

524
00:45:43,740 --> 00:45:46,869
You mean like friends
becoming something more than friends?

525
00:45:47,494 --> 00:45:49,663
Yeah, because I mean, come on.

526
00:45:49,746 --> 00:45:54,001
The person you invite to go
strawberry picking is someone…

527
00:45:54,918 --> 00:45:56,503
A little more than just friends.

528
00:45:57,921 --> 00:45:58,922
I guess so.

529
00:45:59,631 --> 00:46:02,342
Yeah, I guess it'd be someone
you're very close to.

530
00:46:11,602 --> 00:46:15,105
By the way, I was invited to come today.

531
00:46:16,565 --> 00:46:18,066
Yeah, I know.

532
00:46:25,324 --> 00:46:28,035
- Can I ask you a question?
- Yeah, what is it?

533
00:46:28,619 --> 00:46:30,454
Isn't it exhausting

534
00:46:30,537 --> 00:46:32,581
having to constantly face
a one-sided love?

535
00:46:33,582 --> 00:46:34,625
Oh?

536
00:46:36,126 --> 00:46:37,920
You've had that kind of experience too?

537
00:46:39,004 --> 00:46:40,756
Yeah.

538
00:46:41,840 --> 00:46:44,051
Is it perhaps still ongoing?

539
00:46:45,385 --> 00:46:46,553
Yes, it is.

540
00:46:48,514 --> 00:46:49,473
I see.

541
00:46:53,727 --> 00:46:55,562
Sometimes I find myself thinking,

542
00:46:56,396 --> 00:46:59,691
"Romance isn't exactly something
that's necessary."

543
00:47:01,777 --> 00:47:04,029
After all, loving someone

544
00:47:04,112 --> 00:47:07,824
is exhausting, painful,
and honestly, it’s the worst.

545
00:47:12,079 --> 00:47:16,208
But I went and fell for someone anyway.
So there's nothing I can do now.

546
00:47:17,042 --> 00:47:18,669
There's no way to escape now.

547
00:47:21,255 --> 00:47:22,923
Because I love that person.

548
00:47:29,471 --> 00:47:31,932
But it's not like she belongs to me
or anything.

549
00:47:32,891 --> 00:47:34,518
Ayana belongs to no one.

550
00:47:36,103 --> 00:47:39,231
So I'm trying to maintain
the correct distance between us…

551
00:47:43,860 --> 00:47:44,820
And…

552
00:47:46,321 --> 00:47:47,239
And?

553
00:47:48,282 --> 00:47:49,199
And

554
00:47:50,617 --> 00:47:52,035
as long as Ayana is smiling,

555
00:47:52,744 --> 00:47:53,662
that's enough for me.

556
00:48:01,712 --> 00:48:02,546
Hey.

557
00:48:03,505 --> 00:48:04,881
Let's all eat these together.

558
00:48:05,882 --> 00:48:08,051
- Ta-da.
- Wow.

559
00:48:08,135 --> 00:48:10,804
- Whoa, it's huge.
- Look.

560
00:48:14,308 --> 00:48:16,476
You love strawberries, huh.

561
00:48:25,777 --> 00:48:29,072
I like strawberry picking
because it's so laid-back.

562
00:48:33,827 --> 00:48:36,204
- Oh. Listen to this.
- What is it?

563
00:48:37,998 --> 00:48:38,874
The other day,

564
00:48:39,708 --> 00:48:44,129
I went to a concert to see this band.
Before the encore, you know how everyone

565
00:48:44,212 --> 00:48:45,547
keeps on clapping?

566
00:48:45,631 --> 00:48:47,257
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

567
00:48:47,341 --> 00:48:50,010
And you know,
if you keep clapping like this…

568
00:48:55,599 --> 00:48:57,267
Try clapping like this.

569
00:49:02,105 --> 00:49:05,359
The band came back onto the stage.

570
00:49:08,987 --> 00:49:10,822
And that's when I realized.

571
00:49:11,323 --> 00:49:12,741
Your hands get itchy.

572
00:49:13,575 --> 00:49:14,701
Why is that?

573
00:49:14,785 --> 00:49:16,578
Yeah, it does get itchy.

574
00:49:16,662 --> 00:49:18,372
Yeah, sure, it does,

575
00:49:18,455 --> 00:49:21,333
but what is it all of a sudden?
Isn't it because of blood circulation?

576
00:49:22,209 --> 00:49:24,461
I see. It's because we're alive, huh?

577
00:49:25,754 --> 00:49:28,048
Wow. You're amazing, Ayana.
You're absolutely right.

578
00:49:28,840 --> 00:49:31,218
My hands wouldn't get itchy if I was dead.

579
00:49:31,301 --> 00:49:33,470
You wouldn't be able to clap
if you were dead.

580
00:49:33,553 --> 00:49:34,471
True.

581
00:49:39,476 --> 00:49:43,438
Congratulations. Happy birthday.

582
00:49:46,483 --> 00:49:47,901
Thank you.

583
00:49:47,984 --> 00:49:49,986
I'm sorry.

584
00:50:09,965 --> 00:50:13,009
THIS DRAMA IS FICTIONAL

585
00:50:13,093 --> 00:50:13,969
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
